musicians that I'm
playing with, and especially
when I'm playing

47:37.888 --> 47:39.557 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with someone like Brad.

47:39.590 --> 47:50.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: I asked for a
demonstration,
and the two launched into some
blues.

47:50.735 --> 48:00.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRAD MEHLDAU: One thing that
Josh does that's
very exciting for me, as an
accompanist, is

48:00.778 --> 48:11.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRAD MEHLDAU: One thing that
Josh does that's
very exciting for me, as an
accompanist, is

48:11.322 --> 48:14.892 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that I throw him a curve in the
middle of
his phrase.

48:14.925 --> 48:18.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, he was starting to start a
phrase that
was a little more conventional.

48:18.696 --> 48:23.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he was going to kind of wrap
it up, OK,
we gave you an illustration, by
returning

48:23.200 --> 48:24.935 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
